This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new family of Bayesian nonparametric models for sequential data. The paper also introduces a novel deep RGP model and a new inference framework, which are both relevant to the field of machine learning. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed model to tasks such as nonlinear system identification and human motion modeling, which are common applications of machine learning. 

The paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed model is a type of recurrent neural network and is therefore relevant to the field of AI. 

The sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a possibility as the paper applies the proposed model to human motion modeling, which is a common task in computer vision. 

The sub-category of cs.SD (Systems and Control) is another possibility as the paper applies the proposed model to nonlinear system identification, which is a common task in control systems. 

Finally, the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possibility as the proposed model is a type of recurrent neural network and is therefore relevant to the field of neural computing.
